  {
    "client_msg_id": "4fe448ff-02ff-45d7-8f28-7caa0a76532a",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Have you noticed a trend where functional, declarative, and imperative languages are slowly adopting the best parts of each other? I see this happening in JavaScript and C# adopting map/reduce and haskell-like pattern matching and destructuring, for example. There was an interesting video about all this, if I can find it.\n\nAlso, I think Rust is like someone took a lot of those ideas and re-did C with them.",
    "user": "UAVCC2X70",
    "ts": "1565194079.084400",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "ec35ac5b251f",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2018-05-22/369438371830_ec35ac5b251f37e26aca_72.jpg",
      "first_name": "",
      "real_name": "Dan Cook",
      "display_name": "",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "dcook0819",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
