  {
    "client_msg_id": "04e9c393-99fb-4890-bfa9-5e1325b4c2e7",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "It's fun to be an early tech adopter, but also risky.  The number of devs, jobs and amount of libs/frameworks is smaller. When the company I was at was being shopped around for acquisitions, some potential buyers wouldn't touch not-java.  Some other jobs I took later made it apparent managers care more about risk than individual productivity.",
    "user": "UM1HH60GN",
    "ts": "1565194431.084800",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
