    "type": "message",
    "text": "These theorem proving projects which can't make a simple program like an analog clock, which is only 150 words of code, are depressing to me, showing how little progress has been made at improving programming. Lots of mathematical jargon like \"cubical syntax\"; near zero utility outside a mathematical conference.",
